This paper deals with consensus control problems for multi-agent systems, which are typically studied in the subfield of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the adjustable convergence speed, which is a common topic in multi-agent systems research (cs.MA). The use of adaptive control and stability theory suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the simulation examples suggest that the paper may be applicable to robotics (cs.RO).
